# Production image tags. SOURCE OF TRUTH for what runs on stage EC2.
#
# This file is rewritten by build-web-back / build-web-front workflows
# every time they build + push a new image to ECR. The rewrite is
# committed back to main as a regular squash-merged commit by the
# photo-feed-bot-v2 GitHub App, which then triggers deploy-host-stage.
#
# Don't edit by hand unless rolling back — use `git revert` on the bot
# commit that introduced the bad tag, that's the cleanest rollback.
#
# Bootstrap value: "bootstrap" is a placeholder that won't resolve in
# ECR. The stack on EC2 won't start until the first real build bumps
# both tags. To prime the stack manually, run build-web-back and
# build-web-front via workflow_dispatch once everything is in place.

API_IMAGE_TAG=9dbf14ed872c
WEB_IMAGE_TAG=ecf369cb722f
